In this article, President Donald Trump delivers a speech on national security and defense. He begins by expressing condolences for the victims of a train derailment in Washington State and emphasizes the need to fix the infrastructure of the United States. Trump then discusses the failures of previous administrations in areas such as trade, nation-building, military funding, and immigration. He highlights his administration's accomplishments, including withdrawing from trade deals, implementing stricter vetting procedures, defeating ISIS, and taking a tougher stance on North Korea and Iran. Trump also emphasizes the importance of economic prosperity, rebuilding the military, and strengthening alliances. He concludes by calling for a "great reawakening of America" and a renewed commitment to American values and greatness.